The estimate considers the individual contributions and assumes no significant steric hindrance or other effects that might dramatically alter the melting point. The predicted melting point is a summation of contributions from these functional groups and structural features, adjusted from the base value of benzene.
Prediction: The predicted melting point would be 5.5 (benzene base) + 80 (carbamate) + 40 (alkyl and branched structure) + 30 (cyclopentyl ring) + 20 (ketone) = 175.5 °C
